Class HashMap<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • HashMap<T>

  • public class HashMap<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Hash table based implementation of a map data structure.

    Implements the map using an ArrayList of generic type T.

    Positions the generic T element in the index of the ArrayList that corresponds to the ASCII int code. Since the possible values of each key within the map will be limited to the ASCII character encoding set, this will be restricted to an ArrayList of maximum size of 128 keys for every possible unique ASCII character values.
